long_name: William K New Sullivan Elementary School
student_growth_description: Student Growth measures the change in standardized test scores between two points in time, in this case between Spring 2016 and Spring 2017. This growth is compared to the average national growth for schools that had similar scores in 2016. A 50th percentile score means the school grew at the same rate as the national average.
student_attainment_description: Student Attainment measures how well the school performed on standardized tests at a single point in time, in this case Spring 2017. This school’s scores are compared to national average scores. A 50th percentile score means the school is performing at the same level as the national average school.
culture_climate_description: This school is “Organized for Improvement” which means that the school has a strong culture and climate with only a few areas for improvement. Results are based on student and teacher responses to the My Voice, My School 5Essentials survey. For more information on this survey and additional measures of school culture and climate visit  https://cps.5-essentials.org/2017 .
healthy_school_certification_description: Students learn better at healthy schools! This school is working towards achieving Healthy CPS. Schools must earn four badges to become Healthy CPS. Learn more by visiting  cps.edu/healthycps .
creative_school_certification_descriptio: This school is Strong in the arts. It nearly meets the goals and priorities outlined in the CPS Arts Education Plan, including Staffing & Instruction, Partnerships, Community & Culture, and Budget & Planning. To learn more, visit  www.cpsarts.org/creative-schools-certification .
school_survey_rating_description: This school is “Organized for Improvement” which means that the school has a strong culture and climate with only a few areas for improvement. supportive_school_award_desc: This school has not submitted an action plan to support school climate and social & emotional learning (SEL).

student_growth_description: Student Growth measures the change in standardized test scores between two points in time, in this case between students' 8th grade NWEA score (Spring 2014) and 11th grade SAT score (Spring 2017). This growth measure compares students' actual SAT scores to expected SAT scores based on 8th grade NWEA score. CPS also measures growth similarly for 9th and 10th grades (see below).
student_attainment_description: Student Attainment measures how well the school performed on standardized tests at a single point in time, in this case Spring 2017. This school's score is based on attainment relative to the combined College Readiness Benchmark score, set by College Board. To learn more, visit  https://collegereadiness.collegeboard.org .

culture_climate_description: This school is “Not Yet Organized for Improvement” which means there are several weaknesses with the school’s culture and climate, suggesting that the school is not set up for success. Results are based on student and teacher responses to the My Voice, My School 5Essentials survey. For more information on this survey and additional measures of school culture and climate visit  https://cps.5-essentials.org/2017 .
healthy_school_certification_description: Students learn better at healthy schools! This school is working towards achieving Healthy CPS. Schools must earn four badges to become Healthy CPS. Learn more by visiting  cps.edu/healthycps .
creative_school_certification_descriptio: This school has an arts designation of Incomplete Data, and may or may not meet the goals and priorities of the CPS Arts Education Plan, but the school has insufficient data available to complete an assessment. To learn more, visit  www.cpsarts.org/creative-schools-certification .

student_attainment_description: Student Attainment measures how well the school performed on standardized tests at a single point in time, in this case Spring 2017. This school’s scores are compared to national average scores. A 50th percentile score means the school is performing at the same level as the national average school.
culture_climate_description: This school is “Not Yet Organized for Improvement” which means there are several weaknesses with the school’s culture and climate, suggesting that the school is not set up for success. Results are based on student and teacher responses to the My Voice, My School 5Essentials survey. For more information on this survey and additional measures of school culture and climate visit  https://cps.5-essentials.org/2017 .
healthy_school_certification_description: Students learn better at healthy schools! This school is working towards achieving Healthy CPS. Schools must earn four badges to become Healthy CPS. Learn more by visiting  cps.edu/healthycps .
creative_school_certification_descriptio: This school is Strong in the arts. It nearly meets the goals and priorities outlined in the CPS Arts Education Plan, including Staffing & Instruction, Partnerships, Community & Culture, and Budget & Planning. To learn more, visit  www.cpsarts.org/creative-schools-certification .

healthy_school_certification_description: Students learn better at healthy schools! This school is working towards achieving Healthy CPS. Schools must earn four badges to become Healthy CPS. Learn more by visiting  cps.edu/healthycps .

supportive_school_award_desc: This school has not submitted an action plan to support school climate and social & emotional learning (SEL).

student_growth_description: Student Growth measures the change in standardized test scores between two points in time, in this case between students' 8th grade NWEA score (Spring 2014) and 11th grade SAT score (Spring 2017). This growth measure compares students' actual SAT scores to expected SAT scores based on 8th grade NWEA score. CPS also measures growth similarly for 9th and 10th grades (see below).
student_attainment_description: Student Attainment measures how well the school performed on standardized tests at a single point in time, in this case Spring 2017. This school's score is based on attainment relative to the combined College Readiness Benchmark score, set by College Board. To learn more, visit  https://collegereadiness.collegeboard.org .

student_attainment_description: Student Attainment measures how well the school performed on standardized tests at a single point in time, in this case Spring 2017. This school’s scores are compared to national average scores. A 50th percentile score means the school is performing at the same level as the national average school.
culture_climate_description: This school is “Organized for Improvement” which means that the school has a strong culture and climate with only a few areas for improvement. Results are based on student and teacher responses to the My Voice, My School 5Essentials survey. For more information on this survey and additional measures of school culture and climate visit  https://cps.5-essentials.org/2017 .
healthy_school_certification_description: Students learn better at healthy schools! This school is working towards achieving Healthy CPS. Schools must earn four badges to become Healthy CPS. Learn more by visiting  cps.edu/healthycps .
creative_school_certification_descriptio: This school is Excelling in the arts. It meets the goals and priorities outlined in the CPS Arts Education Plan, including Staffing & Instruction, Partnerships, Community & Culture, and Budget & Planning. To learn more, visit  www.cpsarts.org/creative-schools-certification .
school_survey_rating_description: This school is “Organized for Improvement” which means that the school has a strong culture and climate with only a few areas for improvement. Results are based on student and teacher responses to the My Voice, My School 5Essentials survey. For more information on this survey and additional measures of school culture and climate visit  https://cps.5-essentials.org/2017 .
supportive_school_award_desc: This school has developed an action plan to support social and emotional learning (SEL). Leaders and staff have assessed their school climate, and they are beginning to adopt best practices to support SEL for all students.

student_growth_description: Student Growth measures the change in standardized test scores between two points in time, in this case between students' 8th grade NWEA score (Spring 2014) and 11th grade SAT score (Spring 2017). This growth measure compares students' actual SAT scores to expected SAT scores based on 8th grade NWEA score. CPS also measures growth similarly for 9th and 10th grades (see below).
student_attainment_description: Student Attainment measures how well the school performed on standardized tests at a single point in time, in this case Spring 2017. This school's score is based on attainment relative to the combined College Readiness Benchmark score, set by College Board. To learn more, visit  https://collegereadiness.collegeboard.org .
culture_climate_description: This school is “Partially Organized for Improvement” which means that the school’s culture and climate has a few strengths, but also has several weaknesses. Results are based on student and teacher responses to the My Voice, My School 5Essentials survey. For more information on this survey and additional measures of school culture and climate visit  https://cps.5-essentials.org/2017
healthy_school_certification_description: Students learn better at healthy schools! This school is working towards achieving Healthy CPS. Schools must earn four badges to become Healthy CPS. Learn more by visiting  cps.edu/healthycps .
creative_school_certification_descriptio: This school has an arts designation of Incomplete Data, and may or may not meet the goals and priorities of the CPS Arts Education Plan, but the school has insufficient data available to complete an assessment. To learn more, visit  www.cpsarts.org/creative-schools-certification .

culture_climate_description: This school is “Partially Organized for Improvement” which means that the school’s culture and climate has a few strengths, but also has several weaknesses. Results are based on student and teacher responses to the My Voice, My School 5Essentials survey. For more information on this survey and additional measures of school culture and climate visit  https://cps.5-essentials.org/2017
healthy_school_certification_description: Students learn better at healthy schools! This school is working towards achieving Healthy CPS. Schools must earn four badges to become Healthy CPS. Learn more by visiting  cps.edu/healthycps .
creative_school_certification_descriptio: This school is Strong in the arts. student_attainment_description: Student Attainment measures how well the school performed on standardized tests at a single point in time, in this case Spring 2017. This school’s scores are compared to national average scores. A 50th percentile score means the school is performing at the same level as the national average school.
culture_climate_description: This school is “Well-Organized for Improvement” which means that the school has a very strong culture and climate, suggesting the school is set up for success. Results are based on student and teacher responses to the My Voice, My School 5Essentials survey. For more information on this survey and additional measures of school culture and climate, visit  https://cps.5-essentials.org/2017 .
healthy_school_certification_description: Students learn better at healthy schools! This school is working towards achieving Healthy CPS. Schools must earn four badges to become Healthy CPS. Learn more by visiting  cps.edu/healthycps .
creative_school_certification_descriptio: This school is Excelling in the arts. It meets the goals and priorities outlined in the CPS Arts Education Plan, including Staffing & Instruction, Partnerships, Community & Culture, and Budget & Planning. To learn more, visit  www.cpsarts.org/creative-schools-certification .

student_growth_description: Student Growth measures the change in standardized test scores between two points in time, in this case between students' 8th grade NWEA score (Spring 2014) and 11th grade SAT score (Spring 2017). student_attainment_description: Student Attainment measures how well the school performed on standardized tests at a single point in time, in this case Spring 2017. This school's score is based on attainment relative to the combined College Readiness Benchmark score, set by College Board. To learn more, visit  https://collegereadiness.collegeboard.org .

student_growth_description: Student Growth measures the change in standardized test scores between two points in time, in this case between students' 8th grade NWEA score (Spring 2014) and 11th grade SAT score (Spring 2017). This growth measure compares students' actual SAT scores to expected SAT scores based on 8th grade NWEA score. CPS also measures growth similarly for 9th and 10th grades (see below).
student_attainment_description: Student Attainment measures how well the school performed on standardized tests at a single point in time, in this case Spring 2017. This school's score is based on attainment relative to the combined College Readiness Benchmark score, set by College Board. To learn more, visit  https://collegereadiness.collegeboard.org .
culture_climate_description: This school is “Not Yet Organized for Improvement” which means there are several weaknesses with the school’s culture and climate, suggesting that the school is not set up for success. To learn more, visit  www.cpsarts.org/creative-schools-certification .
school_survey_rating_description: This school is “Well-Organized for Improvement” which means that the school has a very strong culture and climate, suggesting the school is set up for success. Results are based on student and teacher responses to the My Voice, My School 5Essentials survey. For more information on this survey and additional measures of school culture and climate, visit  https://cps.5-essentials.org/2017 .
supportive_school_award_desc: This school has developed an action plan to support social and emotional learning (SEL). Leaders and staff have assessed their school climate, and they are beginning to adopt best practices to support SEL for all students.

student_growth_description: Student Growth measures the change in standardized test scores between two points in time, in this case between Spring 2016 and Spring 2017. This growth is compared to the average national growth for schools that had similar scores in 2016. A 50th percentile score means the school grew at the same rate as the national average.
student_attainment_description: Student Attainment measures how well the school performed on standardized tests at a single point in time, in this case Spring 2017. This school’s scores are compared to national average scores. A 50th percentile score means the school is performing at the same level as the national average school.
culture_climate_description: This school is “Well-Organized for Improvement” which means that the school has a very strong culture and climate, suggesting the school is set up for success. Results are based on student and teacher responses to the My Voice, My School 5Essentials survey. For more information on this survey and additional measures of school culture and climate, visit  https://cps.5-essentials.org/2017 .
healthy_school_certification_description: Students learn better at healthy schools! This school is working towards achieving Healthy CPS. Schools must earn four badges to become Healthy CPS. Learn more by visiting  cps.edu/healthycps .

supportive_school_award_desc: This school has put in place systems and structures to support social and emotional learning (SEL). This may include SEL action plans, ongoing training for teachers and staff, partnerships with community organizations, time for SEL in the master schedule, and/or targeted and intensive SEL services.

student_growth_description: Student Growth measures the change in standardized test scores between two points in time, in this case between students' 8th grade NWEA score (Spring 2014) and 11th grade SAT score (Spring 2017). This growth measure compares students' actual SAT scores to expected SAT scores based on 8th grade NWEA score. CPS also measures growth similarly for 9th and 10th grades (see below).
student_attainment_description: Student Attainment measures how well the school performed on standardized tests at a single point in time, in this case Spring 2017. This school's score is based on attainment relative to the combined College Readiness Benchmark score, set by College Board. To learn more, visit  https://collegereadiness.collegeboard.org .

student_growth_description: Student Growth measures the change in standardized test scores between two points in time, in this case between Spring 2016 and Spring 2017. This growth is compared to the average national growth for schools that had similar scores in 2016. A 50th percentile score means the school grew at the same rate as the national average.
student_attainment_description: Student Attainment measures how well the school performed on standardized tests at a single point in time, in this case Spring 2017. This school’s scores are compared to national average scores. A 50th percentile score means the school is performing at the same level as the national average school.
culture_climate_description: This school is “Organized for Improvement” which means that the school has a strong culture and climate with only a few areas for improvement. Results are based on student and teacher responses to the My Voice, My School 5Essentials survey. For more information on this survey and additional measures of school culture and climate visit  https://cps.5-essentials.org/2017 .
healthy_school_certification_description: Students learn better at healthy schools! This school is working towards achieving Healthy CPS. Schools must earn four badges to become Healthy CPS. Learn more by visiting  cps.edu/healthycps .
creative_school_certification_descriptio: This school is Strong in the arts. To learn more, visit  www.cpsarts.org/creative-schools-certification .
school_survey_rating_description: This school is “Organized for Improvement” which means that the school has a strong culture and climate with only a few areas for improvement. student_growth_description: Student Growth measures the change in standardized test scores between two points in time, in this case between students' 8th grade NWEA score (Spring 2014) and 11th grade SAT score (Spring 2017). student_attainment_description: Student Attainment measures how well the school performed on standardized tests at a single point in time, in this case Spring 2017. long_name: Infinity Math Science and Technology High School
student_growth_description: Student Growth measures the change in standardized test scores between two points in time, in this case between students' 8th grade NWEA score (Spring 2014) and 11th grade SAT score (Spring 2017). This growth measure compares students' actual SAT scores to expected SAT scores based on 8th grade NWEA score. CPS also measures growth similarly for 9th and 10th grades (see below).
student_attainment_description: Student Attainment measures how well the school performed on standardized tests at a single point in time, in this case Spring 2017. It meets the goals and priorities outlined in the CPS Arts Education Plan, including Staffing & Instruction, Partnerships, Community & Culture, and Budget & Planning. To learn more, visit  www.cpsarts.org/creative-schools-certification .
school_survey_rating_description: This school is “Well-Organized for Improvement” which means that the school has a very strong culture and climate, suggesting the school is set up for success. Results are based on student and teacher responses to the My Voice, My School 5Essentials survey. For more information on this survey and additional measures of school culture and climate, visit  https://cps.5-essentials.org/2017 .
supportive_school_award_desc: This school has put in place systems and structures to support social and emotional learning (SEL). This may include SEL action plans, ongoing training for teachers and staff, partnerships with community organizations, time for SEL in the master schedule, and/or targeted and intensive SEL services.

long_name: Frederick A Douglass Academy High School
student_growth_description: Student Growth measures the change in standardized test scores between two points in time, in this case between students' 8th grade NWEA score (Spring 2014) and 11th grade SAT score (Spring 2017). This growth measure compares students' actual SAT scores to expected SAT scores based on 8th grade NWEA score. CPS also measures growth similarly for 9th and 10th grades (see below).
student_attainment_description: Student Attainment measures how well the school performed on standardized tests at a single point in time, in this case Spring 2017. This school's score is based on attainment relative to the combined College Readiness Benchmark score, set by College Board. To learn more, visit  https://collegereadiness.collegeboard.org .

student_growth_description: Student Growth measures the change in standardized test scores between two points in time, in this case between Spring 2016 and Spring 2017. student_attainment_description: Student Attainment measures how well the school performed on standardized tests at a single point in time, in this case Spring 2017. This school’s scores are compared to national average scores. A 50th percentile score means the school is performing at the same level as the national average school.

school_survey_rating_description: This school is “Well-Organized for Improvement” which means that the school has a very strong culture and climate, suggesting the school is set up for success. Results are based on student and teacher responses to the My Voice, My School 5Essentials survey. For more information on this survey and additional measures of school culture and climate, visit  https://cps.5-essentials.org/2017 .
supportive_school_award_desc: This school has developed an action plan to support social and emotional learning (SEL). Leaders and staff have assessed their school climate, and they are beginning to adopt best practices to support SEL for all students.

student_growth_description: Student Growth measures the change in standardized test scores between two points in time, in this case between Spring 2016 and Spring 2017. This growth is compared to the average national growth for schools that had similar scores in 2016. A 50th percentile score means the school grew at the same rate as the national average.
student_attainment_description: Student Attainment measures how well the school performed on standardized tests at a single point in time, in this case Spring 2017. This school’s scores are compared to national average scores. A 50th percentile score means the school is performing at the same level as the national average school.
culture_climate_description: This school is “Organized for Improvement” which means that the school has a strong culture and climate with only a few areas for improvement. Results are based on student and teacher responses to the My Voice, My School 5Essentials survey. For more information on this survey and additional measures of school culture and climate visit  https://cps.5-essentials.org/2017 .

student_attainment_description: Student Attainment measures how well the school performed on standardized tests at a single point in time, in this case Spring 2017. This school's score is based on attainment relative to the combined College Readiness Benchmark score, set by College Board. To learn more, visit  https://collegereadiness.collegeboard.org .
culture_climate_description: This school is “Moderately Organized for Improvement” which means that the school has both strengths and weaknesses in their culture and climate. Results are based on student and teacher responses to the My Voice, My School 5Essentials survey. For more information on this survey and additional measures of school culture and climate visit  https://cps.5-essentials.org/2017 .
healthy_school_certification_description: Students learn better at healthy schools! This school is working towards achieving Healthy CPS. Schools must earn four badges to become Healthy CPS. Learn more by visiting  cps.edu/healthycps .

long_name: John Hancock College Preparatory High School
student_growth_description: Student Growth measures the change in standardized test scores between two points in time, in this case between students' 8th grade NWEA score (Spring 2014) and 11th grade SAT score (Spring 2017). This growth measure compares students' actual SAT scores to expected SAT scores based on 8th grade NWEA score. CPS also measures growth similarly for 9th and 10th grades (see below).
student_attainment_description: Student Attainment measures how well the school performed on standardized tests at a single point in time, in this case Spring 2017. This growth is compared to the average national growth for schools that had similar scores in 2016. A 50th percentile score means the school grew at the same rate as the national average.
student_attainment_description: Student Attainment measures how well the school performed on standardized tests at a single point in time, in this case Spring 2017. This school’s scores are compared to national average scores. A 50th percentile score means the school is performing at the same level as the national average school.
culture_climate_description: This school is “Moderately Organized for Improvement” which means that the school has both strengths and weaknesses in their culture and climate. Results are based on student and teacher responses to the My Voice, My School 5Essentials survey. For more information on this survey and additional measures of school culture and climate visit  https://cps.5-essentials.org/2017 .

student_attainment_description: Student Attainment measures how well the school performed on standardized tests at a single point in time, in this case Spring 2017. This school’s scores are compared to national average scores. A 50th percentile score means the school is performing at the same level as the national average school.
culture_climate_description: This school is “Partially Organized for Improvement” which means that the school’s culture and climate has a few strengths, but also has several weaknesses. Results are based on student and teacher responses to the My Voice, My School 5Essentials survey. For more information on this survey and additional measures of school culture and climate visit  https://cps.5-essentials.org/2017
healthy_school_certification_description: Students learn better at healthy schools! This school is working towards achieving Healthy CPS. Schools must earn four badges to become Healthy CPS. Learn more by visiting  cps.edu/healthycps .
creative_school_certification_descriptio: This school is Excelling in the arts.
